SECOND AMENDED & RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS SECOND AMENDED & RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is dated as of November 18, 2021 (the “Effective Date”), by and among Sky River LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Sky River Transmission”), Sky River Wind, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Sky River Wind”), and North Sky River Energy, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“North Sky”). Sky River Transmission, Sky River Wind and North Sky may be referred to herein individually as a “Party” and collectively as the “Parties.”
RECITALS
WHEREAS, Sky River Wind owns and operates a wind turbine electrical generation facility having an aggregate nameplate rating of approximately 60.2 MWs on a site located in Kern County, California (the “Sky River Wind Project”);
WHEREAS, North Sky owns and operates a wind turbine electrical generation facility having an aggregate nameplate rating of approximately 162 MWs on a site located in Kern County, California (the “North Sky Project”, each of the Sky River Wind Project and North Sky Project, a “Project” and collectively, the “Projects”);
WHEREAS, Sky River Transmission owns, leases and/or operates certain personal property, real property, fixtures, easements, equipment and facilities described in Exhibit A attached hereto (the “Shared Facilities”) that are necessary for the operation and maintenance of the Sky River Wind Project and the North Sky Project;
WHEREAS, concurrently with the execution of this Agreement, Sky River Transmission, North Sky and Sky River Wind shall enter into an Amended and Restated T-Line Operation and Maintenance Agreement dated as of the date hereof (the “Amended and Restated T-Line O&M Agreement”) with NextEra Energy Operating Services, LLC (the “Operator”) pursuant to which the Operator will operate and maintain the Shared Facilities and which amends and restates the T-Line Operation and Maintenance Agreement dated as of June 25, 2013, by and among Sky River Transmission, North Sky and Operator;
WHEREAS, Sky River Transmission and Sky River Wind shall enter into a Wind Lease and Easement Agreement for the land on which the substation for the Sky River Wind Project (the “Sky River Wind Substation”) shall be located, and neither the land subject to such agreement nor the Sky River Wind Substation are Shared Facilities or subject to this Agreement;
WHEREAS, Sky River Transmission desires to grant North Sky and Sky River Wind the right to utilize the Shared Facilities, on the terms and conditions set forth herein; and
WHEREAS, as of the Effective Date, this Agreement amends and restates in its entirety the Amended & Restated Shared Facilities Agreement, dated as of June 25, 2013, by and between Sky River Transmission and North Sky.
NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows:
AGREEMENT
TERM; EARLY TERMINATION.
The term of this Agreement (the “Term”) shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties or (b) pursuant to Section 1.2.
This Agreement shall terminate automatically, without further action by the Parties other than any required regulatory filings and without further liability of one Party to the other, upon the date that each of North Sky and Sky River Wind or their respective successors and assigns has permanently ceased operation of the North Sky Project and the Sky River Wind Project, respectively, for the production of electric energy.
GRANT OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS.
During the Term, Sky River Transmission hereby grants to North Sky, on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with North Sky's ownership, operation and maintenance of the North Sky Project.
During the Term, Sky River Transmission hereby grants to Sky River Wind, on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with Sky River Wind’s ownership, operation and maintenance of the Sky River Wind Project.
Sky River Transmission hereby acknowledges and agrees that North Sky's right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities is essential to the production of electric energy by the North Sky Project.
Sky River Transmission hereby acknowledges and agrees that Sky River Wind’s right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities is essential to the production of electric energy by the Sky River Wind Project.
The right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities granted to North Sky hereunder shall vest in North Sky as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title or leasehold interest in the Shared Facilities. Sky River Transmission hereby grants to North Sky a security interest in the personal property comprising the Shared Transmission Facilities.
The right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities granted to Sky River Wind hereunder shall vest in Sky River Wind as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title or leasehold interest in the Shared Facilities. Sky River Transmission hereby grants to Sky River Wind a security interest in the personal property comprising the Shared Facilities.
Except as set forth in Sections 6.7 and 6.8, North Sky shall not assign or transfer the rights granted hereunder, or grant any permission, license, right of way or similar right to the rights granted hereunder, without the prior written consent of Sky River Transmission, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed.
Except as set forth in Sections 6.7 and 6.8, Sky River Wind shall not assign or transfer the rights granted hereunder, or grant any permission, license, right of way or similar right to the rights granted hereunder, without the prior written consent of Sky River Transmission, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed.
NATURE OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS.
Each Party agrees that the rights of Sky River Wind and North Sky to access and utilize the Shared Facilities shall be on a pro rata and pari passu basis with each other for the ownership, operation and maintenance of their respective Projects (based on the relative nameplate rating of their respective Projects as of the date hereof, as set forth in the Recitals to this Agreement), and to the extent that the Shared Facilities are not capable of fully accommodating the joint utilization by both Projects at any time as necessary to permit the full delivery of energy from such Projects (including as a result of a curtailment for any reason), then the respective rights of North Sky and Sky River Wind to access and utilize the Shared Facilities shall be reduced on a pro rata and pari passu basis, unless the cause thereof is a material breach by either Sky River Wind or North Sky of its obligations under this Agreement, in which case, the non-breaching party shall have a priority right to use and access the Shared Facilities.
Sky River Transmission shall provide, or cause Operator to provide, Sky River Wind and North Sky prompt notice detailing the cause and duration of any such reduction to North Sky or Sky River Wind’s right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities.
COSTS AND EXPENSES.
Sky River Transmission shall be responsible for the ownership and possession of the Shared Facilities and, through its supervision and enforcement of the Amended and Restated T-Line O&M Agreement, the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities (the “O&M Services”), which Sky River Transmission shall cause the Operator to perform pursuant to the Amended and Restated T-Line O&M Agreement. The costs and expenses related to the O&M Services shall be the responsibility of Sky River Wind; provided that pursuant to the Amended and Restated T-Line O&M Agreement, North Sky shall have the right to cure payment defaults of Sky River Wind thereunder in order to ensure uninterrupted provision of the O&M Services.
Sky River Transmission has contracted with the Operator to perform the O&M Services in a manner consistent with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Law and Regulation and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the NS LGIA or the SR LGIA, as applicable.
Sky River Transmission shall obtain a title insurance policy insuring Sky River Transmission’s interest in the real property underlying the Shared Facilities (the “Title Policy”). Such Title Policy shall be paid for by Sky River Wind. If Sky River Transmission receives any proceeds under the Title Policy, Sky River Transmission shall apply such proceeds toward curing the relevant title defect, including by obtaining alternate land rights and relocating any affected Shared Facilities.
CHANGE IN LAW
In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Sky River Wind Project or the North Sky Project, or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement.
MISCELLANEOUS
6.1 Agreement to Cooperate. Each Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with the other Party so that, subject to the terms of this Agreement, each of the Sky River Wind Project and the North Sky Project benefits from the full utilization and enjoyment of the Shared Facilities as is necessary for the efficient operation of each Project.
Relationship of Parties. (a) The Parties do not intend to create hereby any joint venture, partnership, association or any other entity for the conduct of any business, and (b) nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize either Party to act on behalf of the other Party.
Non-Interference. Each Party agrees not to interfere with the reasonable and necessary utilization of the Shared Facilities by each other Party as permitted hereunder.
Modification and Amendment. The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by each Party.
Waiver. The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party's right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect.
Enforceability. Any provision of this Agreement that is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of such remaining provisions hereof.
Transfer of Shared Facilities. Except as set forth in this Section 6.7 and Section 6.8, each of Sky River Wind and Sky River Transmission may not transfer, sell, assign or sub-lease its ownership interest in the Shared Facilities or any portion thereof without the prior written consent of each other Party; provided, however, that no such consent shall be required for a transfer of any Shared Facilities between Sky River Wind and Sky River Transmission.
Assignment. No Party may assign its rights or obligations hereunder without the prior written consent of the other Party; provided, that any Party may collaterally assign this Agreement to any entity, or such entity's agent, in connection with a financing or a refinancing that is directly or indirectly secured in whole or in part by the Sky River Wind Project or the North Sky Project, as applicable, and any actual assignment or transfer to another party arising from the realization upon any such collateral assignment (including, without limitation, any purchaser at a foreclosure sale) shall also be permitted without the prior written consent of the other Parties. In connection with the collateral assignment of this Agreement pursuant to the financing of the Sky River Wind Project, Sky River Wind agrees to use commercially reasonable efforts to obtain a non-disturbance agreement for the benefit of North Sky from the collateral agent in its financing and, upon the collateral assignment of this Agreement pursuant to any financing of the North Sky Project, North Sky agrees to undertake the same for the benefit of Sky River Wind. This Agreement shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of successors and permitted assigns of the Parties hereto.
Governing Law. This Agreement shall be governed by and constructed in accordance with the laws of the State of California without regard to its conflict of laws provisions.
Inspection of Records. Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Shared Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times.
Specific Performance. Each Party agrees that irreparable damage for which monetary damages, even if available, would not be an adequate remedy, would occur in the event that any Party does not perform the provisions of this Agreement in accordance with its specified terms or otherwise breach such provisions. It is accordingly agreed that any non-breaching Party shall be entitled to an injunction, specific performance and other equitable relief to prevent breaches of this Agreement and to enforce specifically the terms and provisions hereof, including with respect to its right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities as set forth herein, in addition to any other remedy to which it is entitled to at law or in equity. Any breaching Party agrees that it will not oppose the granting of an injunction, specific performance and other equitable relief on the basis that the non-breaching Parties have an adequate remedy at law. The remedy of the injunction, specific performance and other equitable relief shall be in addition to any other remedy to which the non-breaching Party seeking such relief is entitled at law or in equity.
Section Headings. The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof
Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument.
Resolution of Disputes. Any dispute or controversy arising under this Agreement, its application or interpretation (“Dispute”) shall be settled definitively and exclusively in accordance with the following procedure.
The Dispute will first be reviewed by one member of management designated for the purpose of each of Party. It is the intention of the Parties that the designated managers shall, within thirty (30) days of designation, devise a mutually agreeable solution for acceptance by both Parties.
If the designated managers are unable to devise an acceptable solution within thirty (30) days, or if the Parties both do not accept the solution proposed, the Dispute shall be submitted to the Chief Executive Officer (“CEO”) of NextEra Energy Resources, LLC for resolution. The CEO may resolve the dispute personally or appoint an individual or a committee to resolve the Dispute. In delegating his authority, the CEO may impose any deadlines or direct the utilization of such procedures, if any, as he deems appropriate. The decision of the CEO or his designee shall be final and binding on both Parties.

SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
The “Shared Facilities” shall consist of the following:
Operations & Maintenance Building and Warehouse: The operations and maintenance building and warehouse owned by Sky River that is reasonably required by North Sky or Sky River Wind in connection with the operation and maintenance of the North Sky Project or the Sky River Wind Project, respectively. Also to provide office space for employees and to store equipment and inventory for the Sky River Wind Project and the North Sky Project, together with any replacement, expansions, modifications, improvements (including the water well) or additions to any of the foregoing.
Equipment: The equipment owned by Sky River Transmission that is reasonably required by North Sky or Sky River Wind in connection with the operation and maintenance of the North Sky Project or the Sky River Project, respectively, to include vehicles and the use and replacement of the used spare parts.
Mandible Switchyard, Transmission Lines, Interconnection, and Fencing: The switchyard (known as the Mandible Substation), the fencing of the switchyard and the associated metering equipment, buses, control equipment and other related equipment of Sky River Transmission that are reasonably required by North Sky or Sky River Wind in the operation of the North Sky Project or the Sky River Wind Project, respectively, the approximately 18 mile long Sky River 220 kV transmission line (known as the Sky River 220 kV Line) from the Mandible Substation to Southern California Edison Company’s Highwind Substation, together with any replacement, expansions, modifications, improvements or additions to any of the foregoing.
Miscellaneous Communications Equipment: Onsite communications equipment used by Sky River Transmission that North Sky or Sky River Wind reasonably requires use of in connection with operations of the North Sky Project or the Sky River Wind Project, respectively, together with any replacement, expansions, modifications, improvements or additions to any of the foregoing.
Access Roads, Easements, Permits and Approvals: The various access roads, easements, permits and approvals (including right-of-way permits and conditional use permits) of Sky River Transmission that North Sky or Sky River Wind reasonably requires use of in connection with access to and utilization of the Shared Facilities and operation of the North Sky Project or Sky River Wind Project, respectively, together with any operation and maintenance, expansions, modifications, improvements or additions to any of the foregoing.
